    "body": "Ran into this as well. It's kind of already supported, just not in a \"stable\" way.\n\nSee [Advanced Config](https://starship.rs/advanced-config/) `TransientPrompt` for your shell.\n\nI set this up for the right prompt with:\n\n```\nfunction starship_transient_rprompt_func(prompt)\n  return io.popen(\"starship module time\"):read(\"*a\")\nend\nload(io.popen('starship init cmd'):read(\"*a\"))()\n```\n\nbut it requires that you have it in your config right prompt as well, or nothing is there to \"rewrite\". (At least in my environment with windows/cmd)",
